{{Infobox building |name = YM Museum of Marine Exploration Kaohsiung |native_name = 陽明高雄海洋探索館 |image = YM Museum of Marine Exploration Kaohsiung.JPG |opening = 28 December 2007 |location = [[Cijin District, Kaohsiung|Cijin]], [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]] |building_type = [[Museum]] |map_type = Taiwan |coordinates = {{Coord|22|35|27|N|120|17|23|E|display=title,inline}} |start_date = |completion_date = |cost = |roof = |top_floor = |architectural = |observatory = |floor_count = |floor_area = |elevator_count = |architect = |structural_engineer = |main_contractor = |management = |owner = [[Yang Ming Marine Transport Corporation]] |website = [http://www.mome.org.tw/english_version/ www.mome.org.tw] {{en icon}} |references = }}
The '''YM Museum of Marine Exploration Kaohsiung''' ('''MOME'''; {{zh|c=陽明高雄海洋探索館|p=Yángmíng Gāoxióng Hǎiyáng Tànsuǒguǎn}}) is a [[museum]] about [[Oceanography|marine]] [[exploration]] in [[Cijin District, Kaohsiung|Qijin District]], [[Kaohsiung]], [[Taiwan]].
==History== After its rental tenure was approved by the Marine Bureau of the Kaohsiung City Government on 18 January 2007, [[Yang Ming Marine Transport Corporation]] established the '''Museum of Marine Exploration''' in [[Cijin District, Kaohsiung|Qijin Harbor]], [[Kaohsiung]]. After refurbishment, the museum was officially opened on 28 December 2007 as the '''YM Museum of Marine Exploration Kaohsiung'''.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.mome.org.tw/english_version/introduction/introduction01.html | title=Introduction of MOME | publisher=YM Museum of Marine Exploration Kaohsiung | location=Taiwan | accessdate=28 February 2014 }}</ref>
==Architecture== The museum is a two-story building shaped like an ocean liner. {{fact|date=February 2014}} Its boat-shaped structure appears as a large ship docked along [[Kaohsiung Harbor]].
==Facilities== The museum has the following areas for exhibitions, etc.{{fact|date=February 2014}}
;First floor * Two exhibition halls * 3D animation cinema * Multi-function conference room
;Second floor * Two open air areas for café and performance area * Viewing platform
